This is a letter from Bruce Strumpf, Inc. to Mr. Andrew V. Podray regarding the monthly report for February 2026 for Town & Country Plaza. The letter details the collection report, receipts and disbursements, and leasing updates.

- Text: February 28, 2026
Bruce Strumpf, Inc.
2120 Drew Street
Clearwater, Florida 33765
(727) 449-2020 Fax (727) 449-2212
www.brucestrumpf.com
Mr. Andrew V. Podray
TC Plaza, LLC
800 North Road
Boynton Beach, FL 33435
Re: Monthly Report - February 2026
Town & Country Plaza
Pensacola, Florida
Dear Andy:
Enclosed is the Monthly Report for February, consisting of the collection report, cash receipts and disbursements,
and the income and expense summary, along with the Ending Receivables, Lease Recap and the Sales Volume
Report.
Referring to the Collection Report, all tenants paid rent, except DTLR#4680, Christian Counseling Center and
Lady of Vision Extraordinaire who all paid after the preparation of the report.
Receipts and disbursements were all small or of an ordinary recurring nature, except receipt of an owner
contribution in the amount of $29,628.15. Check #6417 to Haggerty Consulting Inc. in the amount of $984.00
represents return of its security deposit and last month's prepaid rent. Checks #6418 & #6419 to Blue Florida
Services LLC totaling $44,761.00 represents payment for atrium renovations, plumbing repairs and install
wood fencing and board up entrance. Check #6420 to American Leak Detection of NW in the amount of
$535.00 represents payment to repair backflows for stores #3 and #310. Check #6429 to American Lock &
Safe Inc in the amount of $734.33 represents payment for lock repair for #E and rekey stores #155, #160, #165
and #172.
Regarding leasing, an insurance company looked at space D in the Plaza Building.
Very truly vours,
BRUCE STRUMPF, INC.
Jill Strumpf
JS/ka
Enclosures
Licensed Real Estate Broker - Shopping Center Management, Leasing and Redevelopment - Member ICSC

